    "updated_at": "2015-07-16T20:29:39Z",
    "body": "Answer to my above question is no they don't.\n\nAlso, I just wanted to point it out for posterity but I think you can accomplish this by using the [remote](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/docs/api/remote.md) api to create a hidden new window and do your work there. You won't be able to send transferrable objects still, but you will have access to the browser apis there and can use them in the hidden window (such as audio apis). You can communicate via ipc with that window.\n"
